The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Friday, April 02, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Friday, April 2, 2004				 																Road to avoid				 																																	Ballygunge Phari to Gol Park. Dug up and barricaded for tram track dereservation.				 																Soiree				 																																	The Ladies of Calcutta, a musical programme featuring Usha Uthup, Anjum Katyal, Lee Alison Sibley, Tanusree Shankar and others, at Tollygunge Club, 7.30 pm.				 																Celeb talk				 																																	Azim Premji will speak on Shaping your destiny at Science City, 5.30 pm.				 																Art-aid				 																																	An exhibition of paintings, Art Camp, by Wasim Kapoor, Partha Bhattacharjee, Avijit Dutta, Pintu Paul, Sanatan Dinda and Ashoke Mullick, in aid of Anubhav at The Oberoi Grand, 7.30 pm onwards.				 																Films				 																																	Select films from Canadas Banff Mountain Film Festival will be screened at the Satyajit Ray Film amp; Television Institute, from 5.30 pm.				 																Spring fest				 																																	Basanta Utsav will be celebrated with a cultural programme on the Calcutta Club premises, at 7 pm.				 																Exhibitions				 																																	Wonder Weaves, an exhibition of Assam silks at Sampas Boutique, on Circus Avenue, 10 am to 8 pm.				 																																	Dhaara, an exhibition of paintings, on view at Academy of Fine Arts, from 4 pm to 8 pm. 				 																																	Sekhar Roys works on view at Galerie 88, from 3 pm to 7 pm.
